cs.DC, cs.CL, cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.SI

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on building a data processing pipeline using open-source big data tools, which involves distributed and parallel computing.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also likely as the paper discusses text processing and sentiment analysis using Twitter dataset.
- cs.DB (Databases) is another possible category as the paper uses Apache Cassandra for storing processed results.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper deals with processing and analyzing large amounts of text data to identify patterns and trends.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also relevant as the paper uses Twitter dataset as a source of text data.
